original: Aldenius, Harry Fredrik Leander, kyrkoherde, Ukna, Nelhammar, f. 12/ 7/06 i Skänninge av Leander A. o. Helga Andersson. G. 35 m. Märtha Holmberg. Barn: Karin f. 42. — Stud :ex. i Linköp. 25, fil. kand. 28, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Linköp. stift 32. Mis;siv i Mjölby, Virserum o. Linköp. domkyr-koförsaml., bitr. stiftsadj. 35, kommin. i Tåby 36, kyrkoh. i Ukna sed. 37. Ordf. i kyrkofullm. o. ’skolstyr.
translated: Aldenius, Harry Fredrik Leander, clergyman, Ukna, Nelhammar, born on July 12, 1906 in Skänninge to Leander A. and Helga Andersson. Married in 1935 to Märtha Holmberg, with one child: Karin, born in 1942. Education: studied in Linköping, received degree in arts in 1925 and theology in 1928, followed by practical theological training and ordination in the Linköping diocese in 1932. Served as a missionary in Mjölby, Virserum and in the Linköping Cathedral Parish, assistant diocesan chaplain in 1935, curate in Tåby in 1936 and parish priest in Ukna since 1937. Chairman of the Church Council and School Board.
